channel.title: CVE Feed for Synology -- Synology Photo Station
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Synology -- Synology Photo Station

item.title: CVE-2016-10331|2024-08-06T03:14:42.900Z -- synology -- synology%20photo%20station
item.description: Directory traversal vulnerability in download.php in Synology Photo Station before 6.5.3-3226 allows remote attackers to read arbitrary files via a full pathname in the id parameter.

item.title: CVE-2016-10329|2024-08-06T03:14:42.953Z -- synology -- synology%20photo%20station
item.description: Command injection vulnerability in login.php in Synology Photo Station before 6.5.3-3226 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via shell metacharacters in the crafted 'X-Forwarded-For' header.

item.title: CVE-2016-10330|2024-08-06T03:14:43.046Z -- synology -- synology%20photo%20station
item.description: Directory traversal vulnerability in synophoto_dsm_user, a SUID program, as used in Synology Photo Station before 6.5.3-3226 allows local users to write to arbitrary files via unspecified vectors.
